The founder of Dubai’s leading developer, Emaar Properties has launched the Ramhan Mega Island Project. The multinational real estate development company’s headquarters are in the UAE. Emaar Properties is a public joint-stock company, which is listed on the Dubai Financial Market. As of June 2021, it boasts a valuation of US$15.5 billion. The company’s portfolio reflects its proven competencies. More especially in shopping malls, leisure, retail, and hospitality as well as properties. The $3.5 billion island project in Abu Dhabi will feature 1,000 branded residences, a marina as well as a hotel. Additionally, it will also feature 1,800 beach villas. The project’s already existing island is about 20 minutes from the shores of the mainland in Abu Dhabi. The Ramhan Mega Island Project strives to offer a ‘natural, raw and untouched’ experience. Read Also: Julphar Residences on Reem Island, Abu Dhabi, Launched Upon completion, the project will include a world-class marine. It will also include state-of-the-art shopping as well as dining. Furthermore, the project will have floating villas and a luxury hotel. In total, eight varying villa layouts and designs will be rolled out. The designs and layouts will range from 265 meters squared to 700 meters squared. While commenting on the project, Alababar said that aside from being complete with everything from nature, the island is also home to turtles, dolphins, and birds. Its additional, and serene surroundings will offer guests and residents an opportunity to experience a quality of life that has never been seen before. He further added that properties that are located by water often are 34% premium on their value. Quite impressively, the project’s launch comes just three months after the launch of the $2.5 billion Durres Yacht Club. Other mega projects include the Marina in Albania. Alabbar concluded by noting that out of all the unique projects over the years, the Ramhan Mega Island Project is truly special.